BARTONELLOSIS - PERU (LIMA PROVINCE) (02): BACKGROUND
**************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Sun 24 Sep 2006
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
Source: GideonOnline.com [edited]
<http://www.gideononline.com>


Regarding the recent posting, it is worth noting that reports of
bartonellosis in Peru are at least as common as those of more
familiar diseases borne by flying insects: dengue and cutaneous
leishmaniasis. See:
<http://exhibit.gideononline.com/Bartonella-Peru.jpg>.

The approximate numbers extracted from the table since 1997 [by Mod.LL] are:

Cases per Year of Disease

Year / Bartonellosis / Cut. Leishmaniasis / Dengue

1997 / 1500 / 2500 / 2000
1998 / 3000 / 2500 / 1500
1999 / 3000 / 4950 / 5000
2000 / 2000 / 5000 / 2000
2001 / 2000 / 5000 / 23500
2002 / 3500 / 7250 / 8500
2003 / 7000 / 7000 / 3500
2004 / 12000 / 6500 / 10000
2005 / 11000 / 6000 / 7000

--
Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
<mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
